Ok, so this is not about gzipped WARCs, but about gzipped archive payloads
inside gzipped WARCs, yes? Note that WARCs that are NOT gzipped (i.e.
&#39;.warc&#39; files rather than &#39;.warc.gz&#39; files) may not playback correctly in
Wayback as parts of the code assume compression and may fail to index the
content correctly.



We did see issues playing back GZipped payloads in Wayback but that was a
while ago (pre 1.7.1 at least), so if that is the problem, I don&#39;t know why.



You could also look at the CDX files that Wayback is generating to see if
that gives any clues as to the problem.



Thanks,

Andy



